snippet: For all her fans and campaign riches, Elizabeth Warren has a lot of work ahead to persuade voters in Massachusetts to oust Senator Scott P. Brown.
abstract: Democrat Elizabeth Warren hopes to persuade voters in Massachusetts to oust Republican Sen Scott P Brown; Warren's fundraising efforts, which include an extraordinary $6.9 million in the first quarter of year, could help combat Republican criticism that she is buoyed mostly by outside support.
lead_paragraph: For all her fans and campaign riches, Elizabeth Warren has a lot of work ahead to persuade voters in Massachusetts to oust Senator Scott P. Brown.

headline.seo: Massachusetts Senate Race Testing Politics of Likability
headline.main: In Massachusetts Senate Race, Testing the Politics of Likability
